22064484,s2,T4,T5,,PGC-1alpha, is a short-lived protein, and the molecular components that control ",PGC-1alpha, turnover and their functional importance in energy metabolism are largely unknown.,Not_a_complex

22064484,s3,T6,T23,"Here we performed a luciferase-based overexpression screen and identified a Ring-finger-containing protein, ",RNF34,", as a specific ",E3 ubiquitin ligase, for PGC-1alpha.,Not_a_complex

22064484,s4,T8,T9,,RNF34, is a nuclear protein that interacts with and ubiquitinates ,PGC-1alpha, to promote its turnover.,Complex_formation

22064484,s5,T10,T11,"Interestingly, ",RNF34, binds to the C-terminal half of ,PGC-1alpha, and targets it for degradation independently of the previously identified N-terminal phosphodegron motif.,Complex_formation

22064484,s6,T12,T13,"In brown fat cells, knockdown of ",RNF34, increases the endogenous ,PGC-1alpha," protein level, uncoupling protein 1 (UCP1) expression, and oxygen consumption, while the opposite effects are observed in brown fat cells ectopically expressing wild-type RNF34 but not in cells expressing the ligase activity-defective mutant.",Not_a_complex
